To instruct the Municipal Accountant, who has the main responsibility to monitor the timely application of Fidelity Bonds, to check the correctness of the amount and duties indicated in the application to be submitted to the Bureau of Treasury; 

To require the Municipal Treasurer and Cashier-Designate to ensure that their actual duties be indicated in their application for Fidelity Bonds, considering that their designations and titles of positions do not clearly state their control over the LGU’s funds; and

To the Approving Officer, to ensure the correctness of all data in the application for Fidelity Bonds before he affixes his signature for approval and prior to submission to the Bureau of Treasury.

We reiterated our previous year’s audit recommendations that Management:

a.	require the Office of the MGSO to complete the conduct of physical inventory of all its properties;

b.	formally create a committee to conduct the proper appraisal of the properties whose value could not be identified due to absence of supporting documents;

c.	require the Office of the Municipal Accountant and Office of the Municipal General Services Officer to fast track the reconciliation of the results of physical inventory against the balances maintained in the books; effect adjustments in the books of account as appropriate.

d.	Henceforth, complete the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor in compliance with the provisions of the NGAS Manual.

We recommended that:

a.	The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer ensure the prompt and complete submission of disbursement vouchers, payrolls, official receipts and related reports pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-006;

b.	The Municipal Accountant maintain printed copies of the General Ledger and Subsidiary Ledgers for each account in compliance with PD 1445 and pertinent provisions of the Manual on NGAS and submit the same to the Auditor for verification.

